        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:57PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Onaka, or 17 miles northwest of Faulkton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brentwood Colony.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
